  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Determine if there exists an integer n such that 2023*n is a power of 2. Use the prime factorization of 2023 to justify your answer."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Determine if k(n)=2 is possible by checking if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b for some integers a, b. Specifically, check if 2023 divides 2^m + 1 for some m. If k(n)=2 is impossible, investigate if k(n)=3 is possible."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent will take the result from helper_1 to see if the minimum k(n) is 1. If not, it will take the result from helper_2 to see if the minimum k(n) is 2. If helper_2 concludes k(n)=2 is impossible, the parent will use the findings regarding k(n)=3 to determine the final minimum value."
}
```

